    "Manual data collection.",
    "About four hundred high-quality images of railroad transmission line scenes were grabbed from the Microbe image library (https://cn.bing.com/images) using Python, and then 412 images of transmission line anomalies were synthesized using Adobe Photoshop (PS) software, as shown in Fig. 2.",
    "Image generation based on artificial intelligence generated content.",
    "In real-world scenarios, obtaining large numbers of foreign object samples for specific railway scenes is a difficult and time-consuming task.",
    "Therefore, to solve the data scarcity problem, a foreign object image generation method based on ChatGPT and AIGC is proposed."
